Share with:
Head of Key Account Management Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Logistics
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Rp. 18.000.000 - Rp. 25.000.000
Created:
02 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of rapidly growing multinational consumer goods company. Our respected client is seeking a sales professional with at least five years’ experience with a respectable consumer goods company for the job of Head of Key Account Management, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Provides guidance to Key Account channel and aligns their targets based on country’s priorities
Coordinates implementation of strategic priorities in CSI/MNC together with global/regional CSI/MNC
Facilitates the development of local Strategic Customers to support budget achievement
Responsible for CSI/MNC/SC budget achievement in the country
Plans and manages portfolio of accounts
Supports local Key Account Teams (through account planning, joined visits to Top customers) and acts as coach for the Key Account Team
Supports and facilitates  Sales skills/process training relevant to the Key Account channel
Actively participates in expert community and fosters collaboration
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree (min.) in any major
5 years’ experience (min.) in sales in forwarding industry with three years at the managerial level
Good understanding of sectors issue in the forwarding industry
Well-developed management skills and collaborative leadership style
Ability to identify customer needs by gathering information and building long-term relationships
Good communication and presentation skills
Conceptual thinking and analytical skills
Computer-literate (Ms. Office is a must, exposure to CRM platform is preferable)
Fluent in English verbal/written communication
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.